ex:tuberculosis a skos:Concept ;
    skos:prefLabel "Tuberculosis"@en ;
    skos:definition "Tuberculosis (TB) is a curable bacterial infectious disease caused byMycobacterium tuberculosisthat most commonly affects the lungs. It causes national epidemics of varied severity worldwide. Forms of TB that are resistant to treatment - multi-drug-resistant TB (MDR-TB) and extensively drug-resistant TB (XDR-TB) - are public health crises and threaten health security worldwide (WHO, 2024)."@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "tuberculose"@fr ;
