    skos:definition "Explosive ordnance, including explosive remnants of war, is interpreted as encompassing the following munitions: mines, cluster munitions, unexploded ordnance, abandoned ordnance, booby traps and other devices (IMAS 4.10) that remain in the environment following the cessation of armed conflict."@en ;
