ex:perfluoroalkyl_and_polyfluoroalkyl_substances a skos:Concept ;
    skos:prefLabel "Perfluoroalkyl and Polyfluoroalkyl Substances"@en ;
    skos:definition "Polyfluoroalkyl substances (PFAS) are a large family of chemicals in which ​multiple fluorine atoms are attached to an alkyl chain within a molecule​. If all possible sites of an alkyl chain are occupied by fluorine atoms, the substance may also be referred to as a perfluoroalkyl substance as in perfluorooctanoic acid (PFOA) or perfluorooctanesulfonic acid (PFOS). (WHO, 2023)."@en ;
