    skos:definition "Typhoid fever is a life-threatening infection caused by the bacterium Salmonella typhi. It is usually spread through contaminated food or water. As of 2019 estimates, there are 9 million cases of typhoid fever annually, resulting in about 110 000 deaths per year. (WHO, 2023)."@en ;
